<h4 align=center>Settings for the $LIST mailing list</h4>
  <input type="hidden" name="list" value="$LIST">

<dl>
  <dt>
  Delivery class:
  <select name="$LIST;delivery">
    <option value="$CLASSES" $SELECTED>$CLASS_DESCRIPTIONS
  </select>
  </dt>
  <dd>The delivery class determines how the messages which are
      posted to the $LIST list are delivered to $VICTIM.
      The following choices are available from the menu:</dd>
    <dl>
      <dt><b>each message as it is posted</b> (each)</dt>
      <dd>You will receive a separate copy of each message.</dd>

      <dt><b>each unduplicated message</b> (unique)</dt>
      <dd>You will receive a separate copy of each message,
      unless it has already been posted to another mailing
      list at $SITE to which you are subscribed.</dd>

      <dt><b>no messages</b> (nomail)</dt>
      <dd>You will receive no mail at all from the $LIST list.</dd>

      <dt><b>resume receiving messages</b> (mail)</dt>
      <dd>If you are currently receiving <b>no messages</b>, you
      will begin receiving messages again.  Otherwise, this
      option has no effect.</dd>

      <dt><i>anything else...</i> (digest)</dt>
      <dd>You will receive the messages bundled in a digest.  
      Each digest has three formats:</dd>
      <dl>
        <dt>index</dt>
        <dd>You will receive a summary of the messages in the
        digest, but not the messages themselves.</dd>

        <dt>mime</dt>
        <dd>Each message will be included as an attachment.</dd>

        <dt>text</dt>
        <dd>Only the text of each message will be included in the digest.
        No message attachments (web pages, images, etc.) will be
        sent to you.</dd>
      </dl>
       
    </dl>

    <p>
    See the $HELP:SET help page 
    for more information about digests and other delivery classes.
    </p>

  </dd>
</dl>

<p>
The delivery class offers several choices, but your other personal 
settings have only two values, <b>on</b> or <b>off</b>.  Press
the checkbox next to the name of a setting to change its value.
</p>

<dl>
  <dt>$ACKDENY_CHECKBOX ackdeny</dt>
  <dd>
    Select this to be notified when your posted messages 
    are denied by the access restrictions  of a list.
  </dd>

  <dt>$ACKPOST_CHECKBOX ackpost</dt>
  <dd>
    Select this to be notified when your
    posted messages have been accepted and are being delivered.
  </dd>

  <dt>$ACKREJECT_CHECKBOX ackreject</dt>
  <dd>
    Select this to be notified when your posted messages 
    or majordomo commands are rejected by one of
    the moderators.
  </dd>

  <dt>$ACKSTALL_CHECKBOX ackstall</dt>
  <dd>
    Select this to be notified when your
    posted messages are being reviewed by the moderators
    before they appear on a mailing list.
  </dd>

  <dt>$ELIMINATECC_CHECKBOX eliminatecc</dt>
  <dd>
    Select this if you do not want two copies
    when someone sends a message both to you and to the list.
  </dd>

  <dt>$HIDEADDRESS_CHECKBOX hideaddress</dt>
  <dd>
    Select this if you do not want your address to appear
    when someone reviews the list of subscribers with the 
    $HELP:WHO command.
  </dd>

  <dt>$HIDEALL_CHECKBOX hideall</dt>
  <dd>
    Select this if you do not want your name or address 
    to appear when someone reviews the list of subscribers
    with the $HELP:WHO command.
  </dd>

  <dt>$HIDEPOST_CHECKBOX hidepost</dt>
  <dd>
    Select this is you do not want messages that you post
    to the mailing list to appear in a public archive.
  </dd>

  <dt>$POSTBLOCK_CHECKBOX postblock</dt>
  <dd>
    If the postblock setting is <b>on</b>, the list administrators 
    have decided to moderate or deny your posted messages.  Normally,
    only the administrators can change this setting.  Questions
    about the postblock setting should be addressed to 
    <a href="mailto:$OWNER">$OWNER</a>.
  </dd>

  <dt>$PREFIX_CHECKBOX prefix</dt>
  <dd>
    Select this if you want to see a prefix which indicates
    the name of the mailing list in the Subject header of every message.
  </dd>

  <dt>$REPLYTO_CHECKBOX replyto</dt>
  <dd>
    Select this if you want your replies to be sent to the
    $LIST mailing list.  Otherwise, your replies may only be 
    sent to the authors of the messages to which you reply.
  </dd>

  <dt>$REWRITEFROM_CHECKBOX rewritefrom</dt>
  <dd>
    Select this if you want to change the From header
    in messages you send to the list.  The From header will then be
    rewritten to appear as it did when you subscribed to the list.
  </dd>

  <dt>$SELFCOPY_CHECKBOX selfcopy</dt>
  <dd>
    Select this if you want to receive a copy of each message
    that you post to the mailing list.
  </dd>
</dl>
<p>
$VICTIM has been subscribed to the $LIST list since 
$SUBTIME.<br>
This subscription was last changed on $CHANGETIME.
</p>
